<subSubSection id="C300A1C27951FF9DBEA67EABC919FEF8" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497951FF9DBEA67EABC919FEF8" blockId="8.[151,1435,190,294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7951FF9DBEA67EABC967FF06" bold="true" box="[151,279,190,216]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Thorax, abdomen and legs predominantly yellow; postcranium black dorsally, yellowish ventrally; male tergite 8 with distal projection truncated. Female without pinnate scales on hind tibia; wing entirely brown infuscated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
