<subSubSection id="C300A1C27951FF9CBEF479BDCB28FBD4" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497951FF9CBEF479BDCA7DFD75" blockId="8.[151,1436,1960,2025]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,152,1460]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7951FF9DBEF479BDC92FF81C" bold="true" box="[197,351,1960,1986]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54A14CEB7951FF9DBF5979BCC9A7F81D" box="[360,471,1961,1987]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Holotype</typeStatus>
male. Frons approximately one third anterior ocellus width. Face slightly wider than frons only at ventral margin. Postcranium black dorsally, yellow ventrally. Antenna with scape and pedicel yellowish. Palpus yellow. Thorax shining yellow with yellow to gray-brown pruinescence. Setae: 4 dorsocentrals; 1 supra-alar presutural; 2 pairs of scutellars (rarely one pair); 3–5 antepronotals; 2–3 tiny proepisternals; 2–5 katatergitals. Legs shining, yellow with apex of mid and hind femora, apex of hind tibia and all tarsi black, except fore and mid first tarsomeres yellow and hind first tarsomere slightly yellow on basal third. Mid tibia with one dorsal seta slightly stout at basal fifth; hind tibia with 4–5 slender but rather short dorsal setae; first hind tarsomere with two longer dorsal setae. Wing distinctly brown infuscated at costal and apical margin (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBF4E7F95C9A8FE44" box="[383,472,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); M 
<subScript id="179EF00C7950FF9CBC387F85CA61FE40" attach="left" box="[521,529,400,414]" fontSize="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript id="179EF00C7950FF9CBC597F85CA00FE40" attach="left" box="[616,624,400,414]" fontSize="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">2</subScript>
veins distinct apically, not evanescent. Halter dark brown to black. Abdomen shining yellow to orange, sometimes black because of internal structures. Terminalia black dorsally, yellow ventrally. Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBFEC7FC5CA43FE34" box="[477,563,464,490]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
) with blunt truncated distal projection. Sternite 8 with small protuberance posterodorsally (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBF517FE2C9C7FDCF" box="[352,439,503,529]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
). Epandrium with anterodorsal and posterodorsal protuberances of subequal length (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBEAE7C08C886FDE9" box="[159,246,541,567]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
). Anterior cercus very elongate and bifid distally; posterior cercus (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBA227C08CC19FDE9" box="[1043,1129,541,567]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
) somewhat rounded, with many slender anterodorsal setae and simple incurved protuberance at margin. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBACC7C51CD25FD80" box="[1277,1365,580,606]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
) with many setae medially, small row of spine-like subapical setae and distal anterior margin developed over shortened paired protuberances.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497950FF9CBEF47CADCA8AFD0C" blockId="9.[151,1436,152,1460]" box="[197,762,696,722]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Size. Body length 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC7950FF9CBFAC7CADC98AFD0C" box="[413,506,696,722]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.9" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="5.9">5.9 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC7950FF9CBCA97CADCA86FD0C" box="[664,758,696,722]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="6.7">6.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497950FF9CBEF47CCACAAAFC63" blockId="9.[151,1436,152,1460]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Female. Frons as wide as anterior ocellus width; face narrower than frons, approximately one third anterior ocellus width. Mid tibia with no stout setae. Hind tibia without pinnate scales. Wing (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBAC77D10CD39FCC1" box="[1270,1353,773,799]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4f</figureCitation>
) wider than in male, entirely brown infuscated with cell dm, CuA 
<subScript id="179EF00C7950FF9CBD747D29CB3DFC94" attach="left" box="[837,845,828,842]" fontSize="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">2</subScript>
and anal margin lighter; posterior margin sinuose. Abdomen somewhat yellow reddish with terminalia black, sparsely gray pruinose. Terminalia with tergite 8 and sternite 8 very elongated (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBC3F7D69CAE7FC48" box="[526,663,892,918]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Figs. 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC7950FF9CBC647D69CA04FC48" box="[597,628,892,918]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="4.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" unit="g" value="4.0">4g</quantity>
–h
</figureCitation>
). Genital fork (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBD657D69CBD7FC48" box="[852,935,892,918]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 4i</figureCitation>
) predominantly membranous with small sclerotized rod and two slightly sclerotized spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497950FF9CBEF47DDFCA8AFC3A" blockId="9.[151,1436,152,1460]" box="[197,762,970,996]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Size. Body length 6.0 mm; wing length 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC7950FF9CBCA97DDFCA86FC3A" box="[664,758,970,996]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="6.6">6.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
