<figureCitation id="1321EECC7950FF9CBD3A7DE5CB22FBD4" box="[779,850,1008,1034]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,258,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[411,1210,1144,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-134@15.[355,1229,1144,1914]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distribution map of species belonging to the Macrostomus ferrugineus species-group with tergite 8 truncated or forked distally. Symbols represent the known collection localities as follows: diamond = M. longipennis, n. sp.; open circle = M. furcatus, n. sp.; open triangle = M. flavus, n. sp.; square = M. fulvithorax; star = M. occidentalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321598/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
